Key Match Events: Bahrain conceded an own goal in the 35th minute after Craig Goodwin whipped in a powerful low cross from the left side.
Mitchell Duke scored a close-range header in the 60th minute after the ball was headed across from Goodwin.
Gethin Jones made his debut for the Socceroos and received his first start.
Pre-Game Insights: Graham Arnold lauded the inclusion of Gethin Jones in the squad.
Sam Silvera was given his first start for his country.
Craig Goodwin praised the team's patience in the match.
Post-Match Reflections: Graham Arnold praised the team's performance as a morale-boosting 2-0 victory before the Asian Cup.
Mitchell Duke expressed satisfaction with gaining important minutes ahead of the Asian Cup.
Gethin Jones reflected on the faith put in him by coach Graham Arnold and his strong club form rewarded with an immediate starting berth.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Bahrain had a deflected cross turned shot in the 68th minute that forced a fantastic save by Joe Gauci in net.
The match took place at Baniyas Stadium in Abu Dhabi on Saturday, 6 January 2024.
